{
  "stem": "20083.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But since my sister was considered an adult, just like my mother, since she was over 21, there was no difference between taking care of either her or my mother.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And nothing could be done.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had to wait many years either to come to the United States, to England, or any other part.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even if they had emigrated to Holland or Belgium, it would have done them very little good, as in the case of Anne Frank's family, who were all arrested later.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not-- as far as discussions are, are concerned, it was always a member of two parties because my father lived with his second wife, and I lived with my mother and sister.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my father and my mother never even got, ever got together to discuss that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There-- I remember about 1936, a Jewish boy friend of mine, a school friend of mine, Klaus Norden, he emigrated to the United States with his family.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was one of the smart ones.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But you have to also realize that at the time, even though there was a, a discrimination against the Jews, we never thought it would end up in a prosecution and gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They thought, either-- like many hundreds of thousands of German Jews, they thought well, Hitler wouldn't last much longer because he's been ostracized by the rest of the world.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they simply felt even if he would last, it couldn't get much worse.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they would have to-- probably couldn't practice their trade anymore, but they could still get by.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And most of them did not even try very hard to emigrate, unfortunately, my family amongst them.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
